the hardest thing in the world, but on this project i gave myself a one week deadline. And I think my efforts speak for themselves.]]></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">Shooter Project</title><link href="http://localhost:4000/game%20development/2023/02/10/Shooter.Project/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Shooter Project" /><published>2023-02-10T00:00:00-07:00</published><updated>2023-02-10T00:00:00-07:00</updated><id>http://localhost:4000/game%20development/2023/02/10/Shooter.Project</id><content type="html" xml:base="http://localhost:4000/game%20development/2023/02/10/Shooter.Project/"><![CDATA[]]></content><author><name></name></author><category term="Game Development" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[A third-person shooter built on the Unreal game engine. The goal of this project was to improve my C++ skills and expand my game development skills into Unreal. I set up the animation blending logic, game loop, enemy AI behaviour and hit scan guns.]]></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">Toon Tanks</title><link href="http://localhost:4000/game%20development/2023/01/22/Toon-Tanks/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Toon Tanks" /><published>2023-01-22T00:00:00-07:00</published><updated>2023-01-22T00:00:00-07:00</updated><id>http://localhost:4000/game%20development/2023/01/22/Toon-Tanks</id><content type="html" xml:base="http://localhost:4000/game%20development/2023/01/22/Toon-Tanks/"><![CDATA[]]></content><author><name></name></author><category term="Game Development" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[A simple tank shooter utilizing both blueprints and C++. Future upgrades coming soon.]]></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">Clash and Dash</title><link href="http://localhost:4000/game%20development/2022/12/11/Clash-And-Dash/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Clash and Dash" /><published>2022-12-11T00:00:00-07:00</published><updated>2022-12-11T00:00:00-07:00</updated><id>http://localhost:4000/game%20development/2022/12/11/Clash-And-Dash</id><content type="html" xml:base="http://localhost:4000/game%20development/2022/12/11/Clash-And-Dash/"><![CDATA[]]></content><author><name></name></author><category term="Game Development" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[To learn the basics of C++ i decided to build a few games using the Raylib library and OpenGL. In this project, we have two arcade style games. A side-scroller (Dasher) where you avoid obstacles similar to flappy bird and a 2d top-down hack and slash (Clash).]]></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">RPG Project</title><link href="http://localhost:4000/game%20development/2022/11/22/RPG-Project/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="RPG Project" /><published>2022-11-22T00:00:00-07:00</published><updated>2022-11-22T00:00:00-07:00</updated><id>http://localhost:4000/game%20development/2022/11/22/RPG-Project</id><content type="html" xml:base="http://localhost:4000/game%20development/2022/11/22/RPG-Project/"><![CDATA[]]></content><author><name></name></author><category term="Game Development" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[A point and click RPG with conventional gameplay systems found in many modern video games. It includes melee combat, simple ai, inventory management, abilities, quests and dialogue.]]></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">Blender Adventures</title><link href="http://localhost:4000/3d%20modelling%20and%20animation/2022/01/12/Blender-Adventures/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Blender Adventures" /><published>2022-01-12T00:00:00-07:00</published><updated>2022-01-12T00:00:00-07:00</updated><id>http://localhost:4000/3d%20modelling%20and%20animation/2022/01/12/Blender-Adventures</id><content type="html" xml:base="http://localhost:4000/3d%20modelling%20and%20animation/2022/01/12/Blender-Adventures/"><![CDATA[]]></content><author><name></name></author><category term="3d Modelling And Animation" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[The day i decided to become a game developer, i learned that being able to do 3d modelling was crucial. In this project, I built several models to learn what is possible in 3d modelling software. This includes a modular dungeon environmental asset, a chess set, and the classic pixar lamp with animation.]]></summary></entry></feed>